headline: GPC Q4 Deep Dive: Strategic Separation and Cost Headwinds Define Transition Year
summary: Auto and industrial parts retailer Genuine Parts (NYSE:GPC) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025 as sales rose 4.1% year on year to $6.01 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.55 per share was 14.8% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
